meta {
  name: POST honk-and-flash (flash mode)
  type: http
  seq: 20
}

post {
  url: {{base_url}}/v1/vehicles/{{vin}}/honk-and-flash
  body: json
  auth: bearer
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{access_token}}
}

headers {
  Content-Type: application/json
  Accept: application/json
}

body:json {
  {
    "mode": "flash",
    "userPosition": {
      "latitude": 47.3901,
      "longitude": 8.2104
    }
  }
}

docs {
  SEAT/CUPRA honk-and-flash. Mode MUST be lowercase "flash" (NOT
  "FLASH_ONLY"). userPosition is REQUIRED — without it OLA returns
  HTTP 400 "internal-error".

  Coordinates truncated to 4 decimals (~11 m). Integration sends the
  vehicle's last-known parked position (verified via pycupra).

  Implementation: cariad/api/seat_cupra.py:command_flash (line ~761).
  Status: WORKING (verified live across multiple users on issue #53).
}
